## TreeNode Structure

### Pure Data
```rust
pub struct TreeNode {
    /// Unique identifier
    pub id: String,

    /// Display label
    pub label: String,

    /// Node type (domain-specific)
    pub node_type: String,

    /// Optional icon
    pub icon: Option<String>,

    /// Child nodes (recursive)
    pub children: Vec<TreeNode>,

    /// UI state: expanded or collapsed
    pub expanded: bool,

    /// Optional metadata (serialized domain data)
    pub metadata: Option<String>,
}
```

**Key Points:**
- No callbacks
- No domain logic
- No action execution
- Pure hierarchical data
- UI state (expanded) separated from domain state

### Builder Pattern
```rust
TreeNode::new("id", "Label", "type")
    .with_icon("📋")
    .with_children(vec![...])
    .with_expanded(true)
    .with_metadata("status:active")
```

**Why Builder:**
- Optional fields clean
- Chainable construction
- Self-documenting
- Easy to extend

